rComments: Although I managed to get an A, I would say this class is pretty hard for a 100 level English class. The reading materials were hard to get through, especially "The Blazing World". However, In Hye Ha is genuinely interested in the subject and tries her best to help students.

Really disorganized, and gave incredibly difficult and intentionally-misleading pop quizzes. Her teaching style focuses more on the plot of books than anything else and really doesn't seem suited to a college-level course, and doesn't include much of anything on Enlightenment culture. She is, however, a kind person, and willing to help if you ask.

For this 200-level course, our final paper had to be 10-12 pages long after increasing from 4-6 and 6-8 page papers for our first and second essay. She made the class unnecessarily hard. Although we did not have a final exam, we were required to give a final presentation over papers we hadn't completed yet. The extra work isn't worth the credits.

Not bad to look at.  Very patient, and as long as you're respectful, she'll be respectful too.  Make sure to attend class and put legitimate effort into the papers, because she's not an easy grader.  Office hours help :)
She made class so frustrating. I never knew what she wanted out of an assignment, and I don't think she really knew either.
She is impossible to work with. I always got the feeling that the students understood the material better than she did. Her manner of teaching is very confusing and unclear.
